			        DEFAULTDLLNAME="BillingUserExceptionCode"
			        DEFAULTCOMMENT="&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial&quot;&gt;This event gives you access to a Hansen.Billing.Bill object named oBill and a Hansen.Billing.LineItem oLineItem for a given Hansen.Billing.Account object named oAccount.&#xD;&#xA;If this formula has been called to evaluate a LevelTwo Exception then object oLineItem will have the details of the Lineitem and object oBill will be null. &#xD;&#xA;For all other levels of exception oLineItem will be null, in case if the details of Lineitem is needed, then oBill.LineItems can be iterated to get the lineitem details.&#xD;&#xA;The formula will validate if the account has met the requirements of a User Defined Exception or not and pass back the boolean IsException as true = Bill is an exception or false = Bill is not an exception.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;"/>
