			        DEFAULTCOMMENT="&lt;p&gt; Formula that returns the Delinquency Manager to assign to the account delinquency. &lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;This method makes available the &lt;i&gt;Account Delinquency&lt;/i&gt; object, named &lt;b&gt;oAccountDelinquency&lt;/b&gt;, which can be used in your calculation to set a &lt;i&gt;System.String&lt;/i&gt; object named &lt;b&gt;DelinquencyManagerEmpId&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For example, if the Bill Type for this Account Delinquency is for Water you can assign a certain Employee ID as the Delinquency Manager:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xD;&#xA;If oAccountDelinquency.BillType.BillTypeKey &gt; 1 AND oAccountDelinquency.BillType.BillType = &quot;WATER&quot; Then&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;DelinquencyManagerEmpId = 200245&lt;br&gt;End If&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;If you have some &lt;i&gt;Bill Types&lt;/i&gt; that have &quot;Delinquency by Bill&quot; then you can also look at the Bill object on the &lt;b&gt; AccountDelinquency&lt;/b&gt; in addition to the above example or by itself:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xD;&#xA;If oAccountDelinquency.Bill.BillKey &gt; 1 AND oAccountDelinquency.Bill.BillAmount &gt; 100 Then&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;DelinquencyManagerEmpId = 300135&lt;br&gt;End If&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;If the &lt;i&gt;Account Delinquency&lt;/i&gt; is part of a &lt;i&gt;Bill Type&lt;/i&gt; that is set to Delinquency Per Bill then the &lt;i&gt;Bill&lt;/i&gt; property on &lt;b&gt;oAccountDelinquency&lt;/b&gt; will be present with a key greater than 1.  The &lt;i&gt;Bill Type&lt;/i&gt; property should always have a key greater than one."/>
