			        DEFAULTCOMMENT="This formula is used to determine if two needs analysis segments should be joined together based on their index values.  If the two segments are to be joined, then they will be combined into a single segment and the new index value for that single segment will be calculated using a length weighted average.&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;BR&amp;gt;&amp;lt;BR&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;The following parameters are available to use:&amp;lt;BR&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;joinSegments - Set to true if the two segments should be joined.  Otherwise set to false&amp;lt;BR&amp;gt;&amp;lt;BR&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;segmentStartFt - Existing segments start point&amp;lt;BR&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;segmentEndFt - Existing segments end point&amp;lt;BR&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;segmentDeterioratedIndexValue - Existing segments deteriorated index value.&amp;lt;BR&amp;gt;&amp;lt;BR&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;newSegmentStartFt - Start point of the segment to be joined to existing segment&amp;lt;BR&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;newSegmentEndFt - End point of the segment to be joined to existing segment&amp;lt;BR&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;newSegmentDeterioratedIndexValue - Deteoriorated index value of the segment to be joined to the existing segment&amp;lt;BR&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;newSegmentIndexHistoryKey - Original inspection index history key for the segment to be joined to the existing segment"/>
