			<record name="Core.ReportsXFormulaReportXFormulaReport"
			        EVENTKEY="0"
			        PRODFAMILYNAME="Core.Reports"
			        BUSOBJNAME="FormulaReport"
			        PAGENAME=""
			        NAME="FormulaReport"
			        NAMESPACE="Core.Reports"
			        METHODPREFIX="CRFR"
			        METHODSIGNATURE="out Hansen.Core.Reports.FormulaOutput output, Hansen.Core.Reports.FormulaInput input"
			        DEFAULTDLLNAME="Reporting"
			        DEFAULTCOMMENT="&lt;div style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Courier New&amp;quot;; font-weight=&amp;quot;thick&amp;quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#00733a&quot;&gt;'' This is an example Formula report type formula shows how to use the ReportManagementService to call and export another report. After the report is exported it then assigns the output with it''s associated properties to the output parameter.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#00733a&quot;&gt;'' This example also accepts the PrimaryKey parameter from the Formula report type setup and passes it to the report to run''s parameter ApplicationKey. The PrimaryKey parameter must be setup in the Parameters -&amp;gt; Component List Parameters. And the ApplicationKey must be setup on the report being called as well in the same place.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#00733a&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#005ce6&quot;&gt;Dim&lt;/font&gt; result &lt;font color=&quot;#005ce6&quot;&gt;As&lt;/font&gt; Result = Result.Success&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 92, 230);&quot;&gt;Dim&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;primarykey &lt;font color=&quot;#005ce6&quot;&gt;As&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font color=&quot;#005ce6&quot;&gt;Integer&lt;/font&gt; = input.Parameters.Item(&quot;PrimaryKey&quot;)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 92, 230);&quot;&gt;Dim&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;reportRequest = &lt;font color=&quot;#005ce6&quot;&gt;New&lt;/font&gt; Hansen.Core.Report.Management.ReportRequest()&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#00733a&quot;&gt;'' Set the name of the report to be called and exported. When you set the Name property it will search for the report under General Reports.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;reportRequest.Name = &quot;CustomReport&quot;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#00733a&quot;&gt;'' The export type is also known as the Report Output and is determined by the report type you have setup. Which means you can set this to any Report Output for the given report type you have chosen.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;reportRequest.ExportType = &quot;pdf&quot;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;reportRequest.Parameters.Add(&quot;ApplicationKey&quot;, primarykey)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 92, 230);&quot;&gt;Dim&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;reportService = ServerApplication.Resolve(&lt;font color=&quot;#005ce6&quot;&gt;Of&lt;/font&gt; Hansen.Core.Report.Management.IReportManagementService)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 92, 230);&quot;&gt;Dim&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;reportResponse &lt;font color=&quot;#005ce6&quot;&gt;As&lt;/font&gt; Hansen.Core.Report.Management.ReportResponse = reportService.Generate(reportRequest)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;output = &lt;font color=&quot;#005ce6&quot;&gt;New&lt;/font&gt; Hansen.Core.Reports.FormulaOutput()&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;output.OutputStream = reportResponse.OutputStream&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;output.ContentType = reportResponse.ContentType&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;output.Filename = reportResponse.Filename&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#005ce6&quot;&gt;Return&lt;/font&gt; result&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;"/>
			<record name="Core.AccessControlXAccessUserXUserEmployeeIntegrationMapping"
			        EVENTKEY="0"
			        PRODFAMILYNAME="Core.AccessControl"
			        BUSOBJNAME="AccessUser"
			        PAGENAME=""
			        NAME="UserEmployeeIntegrationMapping"
			        NAMESPACE="Core.AccessControl"
			        METHODPREFIX="UEIM"
			        METHODSIGNATURE="Hansen.Core.AccessControl.IAccessUser user, System.Object sourceInformation"
			        DEFAULTDLLNAME="Core.AccessControl"
			        DEFAULTCOMMENT="&lt;p&gt;This event is used to handle transformations of user, employee, contact, and contact identity information being imported into IPS from an external source.  It is intended to allow for handling of more complex scenarios where there is not a one-to-one mapping of data fields or to handle differences in formatting.  The IPS AccessUser business object is available to set the imported data into.  The sourceInformation object provides the incoming data from the source.  For imports from the IFS Attribute Service, sourceInformation object will be a Hansen.Core.Net.IonApi.ClientServices.Ifs.UserResponse object.  For imports from GHR, the sourceInformation will be a Hansen.Core.Net.IonApi.ClientServices.Ghr.EmployeeResponse object.  &lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;'Example of setting the IPS Employee Department code from the Department in the IFS Attribute Service.&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;if TypeOf sourceInformation is Hansen.Core.Net.IonApi.ClientServices.Ifs.UserResponse then&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Dim ifsUserInfo as Hansen.Core.Net.IonApi.ClientServices.Ifs.UserResponse&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;ifsUserInfo = sourceInformation&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;if ifsUserInfo.Department = &quot;Development&quot; then&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;user.Employee.Department.Code = &quot;DEV&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;else&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;user.Employee.Department.Code = &quot; &quot;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;end if&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;end if&lt;/p&gt;"/>
			<record name="CDR.BuildingXBuildingApplicationXCustomValidatePortalElectronicPlans"
			        EVENTKEY="0"
			        PRODFAMILYNAME="CDR.Building"
			        BUSOBJNAME="BuildingApplication"
			        PAGENAME=""
			        NAME="CustomValidatePortalElectronicPlans"
			        NAMESPACE="CDR.Building"
			        METHODPREFIX="CVPEP"
			        METHODSIGNATURE="Hansen.CDR.Building.IBuildingApplication BuildingApplication"
			        DEFAULTDLLNAME="CDRBuilding"
			        DEFAULTCOMMENT="&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;This event is defined to custom validate data entered by the user in the submit instrument portlet in portal. This event is invoked when user leaves the electronic plans tab to prevent them from going forward if invalid data is entered.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;All validation messages should be created as a Hansen.Core.Result with ResultSeverity equal to UserError.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;A validation message can be displayed on the control level by adding the portal control id to the properties list of the Result. If a portal control is not added to the properties list, the validation message will display at the top of the page.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;The following example will create a page level validation message&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Dim res as Hansen.Core.Result = Result.Success&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;If BuildingApplication.ApplicationType.ApplicationType = &amp;amp;quot;SFD&amp;amp;quot; Then&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;amp;apos;Page level message&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;amp;nbsp; If (TypeOf BuildingApplication.Parent Is Hansen.Portal.IInstrument) Then&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;amp;nbsp; &amp;amp;nbsp;Dim instrument as Hansen.Portal.IInstrument&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;amp;nbsp; &amp;amp;nbsp;instrument = CType(BuildingApplication.Parent, Hansen.Portal.IInstrument)&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;amp;nbsp; &amp;amp;nbsp; If ( instrument.ReadyToSubmit = False) Then&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;amp;nbsp; &amp;amp;nbsp; &amp;amp;nbsp; &amp;amp;nbsp; Dim resApp as Hansen.Core.Result = new Result(1, ResultSeverity.UserError, &amp;amp;quot;You must upload the required files before continuing.&amp;amp;quot;)&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;amp;nbsp; &amp;amp;nbsp; &amp;amp;nbsp; &amp;amp;nbsp; res += resApp &amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;amp;nbsp; &amp;amp;nbsp; End if&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;amp;nbsp;End If&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;End If&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;return res&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;"/>
